Description:
Bright and spacious apartment on the banks of Merri Creek.
Filled with natural light, and situated in a quiet, secluded court location overlooking Merri Creek, this over-sized one bedroom apartment boasts approximately 87m2 of living space and places you in the iconic Pentridge estate.
A short walk to Batman train station, trams along Nicholson Street and Sydney Road and Merri Creek bike trails make getting around a breeze, and easy access to the picturesque Coburg Lake, Sydney Road shops and cafes, and the Drive-in Cinema deliver on location and lifestyle.
Situated on the first floor, east-facing floor to ceiling windows take full advantage of the sunrise, and the spacious balcony overlooking Merri Creek is perfect for entertaining and relaxing. With secure underground parking and storage unit, resort-style amenities include communal pool and barbecue area overlooking the park, and automatic gates, intercom system and lift access.
Inside, the space easily switches between airy open-plan living and dining areas that draw the outdoors inside, to cosy seclusion, with double roller blinds, split system heating and cooling and panel heaters providing privacy and comfort.
European appliances and generous bench space define the kitchen, with the bedroom enjoying built-in robes, ensuite bathroom, and an uninterrupted view of parkland.
Clever and ample storage means no compromising on maximal use of space, and separate laundry and powder room cater for convenience and guests.
Internal area: approximately 74m2
Balcony area: approximately 13m2
Total area: approximately 87m2 (plus car space and storage unit)
Phone enquiry code for this property: 6656

Description:
Fuss Free And Close To Everything
Offering exciting entry to a premium Coburg locale, this lovingly maintained two bedroom villa unit promises everything within easy reach. Nestled in a quiet court, yet boasting immediate access to the Upfield Bike Path and positioned a short stroll to O'Hea's Bakery, Coburg Farmers Market, Coburg Lake Reserve, Coburg Station, buses and the cosmopolitan cafes and speciality shopping of Sydney Road, a vibrant lifestyle is guaranteed. Perfectly comfortable, this bright unit features a generous lounge flowing to a neat kitchen/ meals with ample storage and electric cooking. A considerable rear courtyard features garden beds and provides a relaxed low maintenance outdoor space to enjoy. Double bedrooms are serviced by a large central bathroom while a separate laundry, gas heater and split system heating and cooling throughout, together with a single garage completes this exciting Coburg starter.

Description:
Delightful Family home In Coburg East overlooking Merri creek
Rarely a property like this comes in the market place so unique in terms of location, size of the block and the quality of the home. Sitting high with wonderful views of Merrie Creek trail surrounded by parklands, this delightful double brick family home is perfectly located in one of the most tightly held family friendly pockets of leafy Coburg. This much loved family home is occupying a large block of approximately 634 sqm of prime land, has the original charming features such as stamped copper kitchen cupboards, intricate floor tiles, textured carpets, Italian chandeliers etc. and a versatile floorplan to suit the needs of growing family boasting three spacious bedrooms, formal lounge, gourmet kitchen overlooking family & dining area. Step outside and be greeted with large outdoor entertainment area with original wood fired pizza oven and well established backyard. Other features include well established front and rear gardens, central heating, split system cooling, multiple storage areas, cellar room, opportunity to restore existing bungalow, all in a quite convenient location close to prestigious local schools, Merrie Creek parklands, Nicholson street trams, buses, Coburg station, Sydney road shopping & cafe precinct etc. offering a unique opportunity to update, renovate or extend (STCA). Enquire today.

Description:
Easy Living or Blue-Chip Investing!
Situated in one of Coburg premier pockets, this single-level villa (one of only six) presents a terrific low-maintenance lifestyle with its generous floorplan, private courtyard and easy access to the area's key attractions. Perfect first home, astute investment or affordable downsize option, the villa's immaculate interior comprises two double bedrooms (both with BIRs), central bathroom and separate WC, spacious front lounge through to the dining area and adjoining kitchen with new stainless steel oven. Add to this gas heating and split-system a/c, full-size laundry, single lock-up garage, plus a wonderfully wide courtyard - north facing and fully undercover. A prime location walking distance to Sydney Road trams and cafes, it's also close to Moreland Station, local schools (zoned to Coburg HS), popular restaurants and cosmopolitan shopping precinct. Move in or rent out - a perfect choice either way! Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Spacious Townhouse with Leafy Outlook
This modern terrace home offers an easy lifestyle for the owner/occupier or a fantastic rental return for the smart investor. Northern light floods into the formal living room with its polished wood floor, while the casual meals/family room opens to a low maintenance rear yard with deck and storage shed. The sparkling white kitchen is equipped with stainless steel appliances and copious storage options. The property offers three carpeted, robed bedrooms; two with balcony access and views over the park in front of the property. The master has a lavish ensuite with spa bath and separate shower, which is accessed via a walk through robe.
Other features include a garage with both internal and rear access, ducted heating, 2 split system air conditioners, separate laundry, downstairs powder room and garden water tank. The location is very convenient being close to the historic Pentridge village, with its shops and cafes, and public transport, bike trails, schools, Sydney Rd and Lake Reserve just a short walk away.

Description:
City Views Await You
Flaunting eye-catching views, this renovated two bedroom apartment features a quiet rear position yet is just moments to dynamic Sydney Road and Coburg Market. There are city glimpses from the living room, eclipsed by impressive skyline views from the main bedroom. Stainless steel cooking appliances and a dishwasher feature in the modern kitchen/meals, matched with a glass splashback and pantry. Reverse cycle heating and cooling offers year round comfort, each of the sunlit bedrooms hosts a built-in robe and in addition to an updated bathroom the home has its own laundry facilities. A covered parking space, beyond a security gate, is another welcome inclusion and within a stroll you'll find trams, trains, popular cafes, shops, Coburg City Oval and more.

Description:
Luxurious Touches
A highly desirable locale and smart facade promise even better things inside, and you won't be disappointed with this beautifully finished two bedroom, two ensuite residence. Bifold doors link the kitchen/meals/living to a northerly entertainer's balcony boasting a remote controlled awning. Expansive stone surfaces successfully team with a dishwasher and 900mm appliances, including a five zone electric cooktop, oven and rangehood, in the exceptional kitchen. Each of the two floors hosts a bedroom with walk-in robe and ensuite, and there's also a study nook on the top floor in addition to a convenient powder room. Further highlights include street frontage, heating/cooling, a full laundry, under stair storage and automatic garage with interior access. Moments to Egan Reserve by the Merri Creek, trams and cosmopolitan Sydney Road, this contemporary home shines.
Alexkarbon Real Estate
122 Errol Street, North Melbourne
